 The Governor Mai Mala Buni-led Caretaker/Extra-ordinary National Convention Planning Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has constituted Primary Election and Appeal Committees for the July 20, 2020 Ondo State Governorship Primary Election. The Governor of Kogi State, Yahaya Bello is appointed Chairman of Primary Election Committee with Olorogun oâ€™tega Emerhor as Secretary while Alwan Hassan, Samuel Sambo, Binta Salihu, Emma Andy, Adebayo Adelabu, Abdullahi Aliyu and Margret Ngozi Igwe are members. The Ondo State Governorship Primary Election Appeal Committee has Chris Baywood Ibe as Chairman and Abdulmimuni Okara as Secretary while Festus Fientes, Okon Owoefiak, ABBA Isah, Umar Duhu, Sani El-katuzu, Osuere Eunice and Emeka Agaba as members. Yekini Nabena, APC Deputy National Publicity Secretary in a statement said both Committees will be inaugurated by the Chairman of the APC Caretaker/Extra-ordinary National Convention Planning Committee, Buni at the APC National Secretariat on Friday.